<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="615" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[813,1456,1620,2030]" box="[813,919,1620,1646]" pageId="16" pageNumber="615">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[813,1456,1620,2030]" pageId="16" pageNumber="615">
The genus was created by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cope" box="[1124,1276,1652,1679]" firstAuthor="Cope" pageId="16" pageNumber="615" pagination="168 - 194" refId="ref17220" refString="COPE E. D. 1879. - On the genera of Felidae and Canidae. Proceeding of the Academy of Natural Sciences, Philadelphia 31: 168 - 194. https: // www. jstor. org / stable / 4060308" type="journal article" year="1879">Cope (1879)</bibRefCitation>
for the species 
<emphasis box="[813,963,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="615">M. brachyops</emphasis>
from the Oligocene of 
<collectingRegion box="[1248,1360,1684,1710]" country="United States of America" name="Nebraska" pageId="16" pageNumber="615">Nebraska</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry name="United States of America" pageId="16" pageNumber="615">United States</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cope" box="[892,1016,1716,1742]" firstAuthor="Cope" pageId="16" pageNumber="615" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref17196" refString="COPE E. D. 1878. - Vertebrate fauna of the Miocene of Oregon. Paleontological Journal 30: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1878">Cope 1878</bibRefCitation>
). One year later, he changed the generic name to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1879" box="[907,1012,1749,1774]" class="Mammalia" family="Nimravidae" genus="Nimravus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="16" pageNumber="616" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[907,1012,1749,1774]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="615">Nimravus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[1073,1121,1748,1774]" pageId="16" pageNumber="615">type</typeStatus>
species is widespread in North America in the middle to late Oligocene (
<bibRefCitation author="Toohey" box="[1282,1442,1780,1807]" firstAuthor="Toohey" pageId="16" pageNumber="615" pagination="71 - 112" refId="ref19218" refString="TOOHEY L. 1959. - The species of Nimravus (Carnivora, Felidae). Bulletin of the American Museum Natural History 118: 71 - 112. http: // hdl. handle. net / 2246 / 1972" type="journal article" year="1959">Toohey, 1959</bibRefCitation>
). A European species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Filhol 1872 a)" baseAuthorityName="Filhol" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[1044,1455,1812,1838]" class="Mammalia" family="Nimravidae" genus="Nimravus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="16" pageNumber="615" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[1044,1286,1812,1838]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="615">Nimravus intermedius</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Filhol" box="[1303,1447,1812,1838]" firstAuthor="Filhol" pageId="16" pageNumber="615" pagination="92 - 94" refId="ref17300" refString="FILHOL H. 1872 a. - Sur les Carnassiers et les Cheiropteres dont on trouve les debris fossiles dans les gisements de phosphorites de Caylux, Fregols, Concots. Comptes rendus hebdomadaires des Seances de l'Academie des Sciences 75: 92 - 94. https: // gallica. bnf. fr / ark: / 12148 / bpt 6 k 30321 / f 94. item" type="journal article" year="1872" yearSuffix="a">Filhol 1872a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
has characters that are so close to those of 
<emphasis box="[1313,1455,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="615">N. brachyops</emphasis>
that Toohey wrote, “I cannot, with the available materials and excellent figures in Piveteau’s study, distinguish any consistent morphological differences between 
<emphasis box="[1319,1456,1939,1965]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="615">N. brachyops</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Filhol" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[861,1018,1971,1997]" class="Mammalia" family="Nimravidae" genus="Nimravus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="16" pageNumber="615" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[861,1018,1971,1997]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="615">N.intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”. (
<bibRefCitation author="Toohey" box="[1054,1249,1971,1998]" firstAuthor="Toohey" pageId="16" pageNumber="615" pagination="71 - 112" refId="ref19218" refString="TOOHEY L. 1959. - The species of Nimravus (Carnivora, Felidae). Bulletin of the American Museum Natural History 118: 71 - 112. http: // hdl. handle. net / 2246 / 1972" type="journal article" year="1959">Toohey 1959: 95</bibRefCitation>
). In Europe, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1879" class="Mammalia" family="Nimravidae" genus="Nimravus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="16" pageNumber="616" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="615">Nimravus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was present in early and middle Oligocene strata.
</paragraph>
